data.text:
I never hear any mention of this album.

I always thought it was a really good album for its time.

I think 867-5309 (Jenny Jenny) is probably the worst song on the entire lp, but the rest of it is really good.

In the same vein as Mellencamp, Michael Stanley and Springsteen for the same time period.

Anyone else like this lp?

Yes, I like it a lot. There was some really good stuff on their first album too.

like this one..

They'll always be known as the 867-5309 band and it's too bad. They definitely had more to offer.

It's sad that the big hit song on it gets all of the attention.

The remainder of that album is wonderful in my opinion.

I particularly like "Shadow on the Road Ahead" and "Bernadiah".
